---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "BC PNP Entrepreneur Immigration 2025: Base vs Regional Pilot";
const description = "Compare the BC PNP Entrepreneur Base Stream vs the Regional Pilot. A detailed breakdown of net worth, investment requirements, and the mandatory community visit.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
      
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="space-y-4 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight">
          BC PNP Entrepreneur Immigration <span class="text-emerald-600">2025</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          For experienced business owners ready to invest in British Columbia. Choose between the flexible Base Stream or the lower-cost Regional Pilot.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
        
        <h2>Which path is right for you?</h2>
        <p>
            B.C. offers two primary streams for entrepreneurs. The <strong>Base Stream</strong> allows you to start a business anywhere (including Vancouver), but has higher financial requirements. The <strong>Regional Pilot</strong> (now permanent) offers lower financial barriers but restricts you to specific smaller communities.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose my-10">
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-0 border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                <!-- Base Stream Column -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 border-b md:border-b-0 md:border-r border-slate-100">
                    <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 text-2xl mb-1">Base Stream</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-6">For Metro Vancouver & Major Cities</p>
                    
                    <ul class="space-y-4">
                        <li class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-50 pb-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Net Worth</span>
                             <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">$600,000 CAD</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-50 pb-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Min. Investment</span>
                             <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">$200,000 CAD</span>
                        </li>
                         <li class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-50 pb-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Ownership</span>
                             <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">33.3% Min</span>
                        </li>
                         <li class="flex justify-between items-center pt-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Location</span>
                             <span class="text-emerald-600 font-bold">Anywhere in BC</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Regional Pilot Column -->
                <div class="bg-emerald-50/50 p-8">
                    <h3 class="font-black text-emerald-900 text-2xl mb-1">Regional Pilot</h3>
                    <p class="text-emerald-700/70 text-sm mb-6">For Communities < 75,000 pop.</p>
                    
                     <ul class="space-y-4">
                        <li class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-emerald-100 pb-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Net Worth</span>
                             <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">$300,000 CAD</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-emerald-100 pb-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Min. Investment</span>
                             <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">$100,000 CAD</span>
                        </li>
                         <li class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-emerald-100 pb-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Ownership</span>
                             <span class="text-slate-900 font-bold">51% Min</span>
                        </li>
                         <li class="flex justify-between items-center pt-2">
                             <span class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-medium">Location</span>
                             <span class="text-emerald-600 font-bold">Participating Only</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Structuring Your Business Concept</h2>
        <p>
            Your comprehensive business concept is scored out of 200 points (separate from your personal registration score). To be competitive, your proposed business must demonstrate:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Commercial Viability:</strong> A clear path to profitability without needing government subsidies.</li>
            <li><strong>Economic Benefit:</strong> How it will add value to the B.C. economy (e.g., introducing new technology, developing new products, or servicing an underserved rural market).</li>
            <li><strong>Job Creation:</strong> A solid plan to create at least one full-time job for a Canadian citizen or Permanent Resident (Regional Pilot) or essentially one job per key staff (Base Stream).</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-emerald-50 border-l-4 border-emerald-600 p-4 my-6 not-prose">
             <p class="text-emerald-900 text-sm">
                <strong>Tip:</strong> High-value sectors like Agri-tech, Forestry, Manufacturing, and Tourism often receive higher consideration than general retail.
             </p>
        </div>

        <h2>The "Exploratory Visit" Difference</h2>
        <p>
            One critical difference is the intake process.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Regional Pilot:</strong> You <strong>MUST</strong> make an exploratory visit to the community and obtain a referral from them <em>before</em> you can register. The community holds the keys.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Base Stream:</strong> You can register directly without a visit (though a visit helps your score).
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Participating Communities</h2>
        <p>
            Over 60 communities participate in the Regional Pilot, including places like Squamish, Vernon, Comox Valley, and Penticton. Each community has its own priority sectors (e.g., tourism, light manufacturing).
        </p>
        <p>Before registering, verify if your target community is currently accepting new entrepreneurs. Some popular communities pause intakes periodically.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 my-6 not-prose">
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Castlegar</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Cranbrook</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Kamloops</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Merritt</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Nanaimo</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Nelson</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Parksville</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Port Alberni</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Prince George</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Quesnel</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Squamish</div>
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">Vernon</div>
        </div>

        <h2>Ineligible Businesses</h2>
        <p>
             Not all businesses are welcome. The BC PNP explicitly excludes certain types of enterprises to ensure economic value. You <strong>cannot</strong> apply if you plan to start:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc leading-loose marker:text-red-500">
            <li>Bed and breakfasts (B&Bs), hobby farms, or home-based businesses.</li>
            <li>Payday loan, cheque cashing, or pawnbroker services.</li>
            <li>Tanning salons, DVD rental stores, or coin-operated laundromats.</li>
            <li>Automated car washes or scrap metal recycling.</li>
            <li>Real estate development or brokerage (unless substantial/strategic).</li>
            <li>Businesses involved in the production or distribution of pornography or sexually explicit products.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>BC PNP Entrepreneur Fees</h2>
        <p>
            The entrepreneur pathways have higher fees than skills immigration:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Registration Fee:</strong> $300 CAD</li>
            <li><strong>Application Fee:</strong> $3,500 CAD (Base) or $2,000 CAD (Pilot)</li>
            <li><strong>Key Staff Fee:</strong> $1,000 CAD (if applicable)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Application Process (Both Streams)</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Preparation:</strong> Research the market (and visit if Pilot).</li>
            <li><strong>Registration:</strong> Submit your business concept and score points.</li>
            <li><strong>Invitation:</strong> Highest scoring concepts are invited.</li>
            <li><strong>Application:</strong> Submit full net worth verification (by a third party supplier).</li>
            <li><strong>Interview:</strong> Attend an in-person interview in Vancouver.</li>
            <li><strong>Work Permit:</strong> Sign a Performance Agreement and arrive in B.C. on a 2-year work permit.</li>
            <li><strong>Nomination:</strong> Once you fulfill the terms of your agreement (investment + job creation), you get nominated for PR.</li>
        </ol>

      </div>
      
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm mt-8">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-xl">Can I buy an existing business?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                    Yes, buying an existing business is heavily encouraged, especially in the Regional Pilot. However, you must show how you will <strong>improve or expand</strong> the business (investing to upgrade equipment, hiring more staff, etc.). You cannot simply buy it and run it "as is".
                </p>
            </div>
             <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-xl">What is the "Key Staff" option?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                    In the Base Stream, if your business is large enough, you can propose to bring one foreign "Key Staff" member (like a specialized engineer or manager) with you. If approved, they also get a work permit and eventual nomination. Note that proposing a key staff member increases the investment requirement from $200,000 to $400,000.
                </p>
            </div>
             <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-xl">Is the language requirement strict?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">
                    For the entrepreneur stream, the minimum is <strong>CLB 4</strong> (basic proficiency). This is much lower than the skilled worker streams (often CLB 7/8). However, better English/French skills will give you more points in the scoring system.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
       <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="text-center space-y-4">
        <a href="/bc-pnp-draws" class="text-slate-600 hover:text-emerald-600 font-bold underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 decoration-emerald-200 hover:decoration-emerald-600 transition-colors">
            See Latest Entrepreneur Draw Scores
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
